description: For sale at Gateway Classic Cars in our St. Louis showroom is a 1972 Chevrolet Camaro.  This beautiful blue Camaro is dressed up as a Z/28 and features a 350 small block with a 4-speed manual transmission.  Complimenting the blue metallic paint is a set of Centerline aluminum 2 piece wheels wearing 195/80R15 front tires and 275/65R15s out back for a nice staggered look.  There is also a cowl hood, SS stripes and a rear spoiler.  Inside you'll find new two tone bucket seats, new carpeting and a new headliner.  There is also a set of Auto Meter gauges for monitoring Oil pressure, Amperage and Water temperature.  Shifting gears is a joy thanks to a Hurst shifter with a white shifter ball.  A Grant steering wheel keeps you in control and an Alpine head unit with some Alpine speakers for your favorite tunes, although you may prefer the note of the engine.  Speaking of the engine, this well-built 350 is featured with tubular exhaust headers, a polished aluminum high rise intake manifold with a Demon carburetor mounted on top.  Dressing up the engine bay is a set of chrome valve covers, chrome alternator, power steering pump and a smoothed firewall.  For more information on this 1972 Chevrolet Camaro, call 618-271-3000 or stop by our St. Louis showroom.  To view HD photos and video, visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com

description: Incredible 1968 SS 396 Camaro with 350 Automatic Transmission, Bucket Seats and Competition Floor Shifter We purchased this car several months ago with a few items that needed to be either completed or fixed. (mainly cosmetic) We have completed all of the items we felt needed addressing and are now offering this beautiful Camaro for sale. Here are some of the things we addressed, the Transmission was slipping so we had the 350 turbo professionally rebuilt and a new torque converter installed. We installed new door weather stripping, a new radiator, new valve covers, new air cleaner and repaired all of the lights, including a new brake switch so that all lights, headlights, parking lights, turn signals and brake lights work correctly. The car has a beautiful metallic gray (teal) paint job that has been done well. The Paint is a base coat/clear coat system, it has a few very minor road chips and a couple of slight imperfections. But from 5 feet away, it looks perfect and in the Sun, the car dazzles and sparkles. The body is very straight, aligns well and appears to be free of rust. There have been a few small patch panels installed, but they were done well and the floor pans are good. The interior is fresh with new deluxe door panels, new carpet, new still plates, new velour and vinyl seat covers with a bow tie stitched into the front two bucket seats. There is a new headliner in the car but it could stand a little stretching to remove what small puckers are in it.
